adjectives.description: overintellectualized (comparative more overintellectualized, superlative most overintellectualized)

entries.meaning: Treated in an excessively intellectual manner
simple past tense and past participle of overintellectualize
examples: It is not unreasonable to argue that the field has been overintellectualized in that many of the representations are based on matrix algebra, latent trait theory, and . . .
